    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 1: \"Slitrk3 selectively induces functional inhibitory presynaptic differentiation in coculture\"\nFig.3: \"Slitrk3 knockdown decreases the density of inhibitory synapses in hippocampal culture\"\nFig.4: \"Slitrk3-/- mice have reduced inhibitory synapse density in CA1 region of hippocampus\"\nFig.5: \"Slitrk3-/- mice have reduced inhibitory synaptic transmission in CA1 of the hippocampus\". Experimental description: - \"Slitrk3 expressed in fibroblasts triggers only inhibitory presynaptic differentiation in contacting axons of cocultured rat hippocampal neurons. Recombinant Slitrk3 preferentially localizes to inhibitory postsynaptic sites.\"\n\n- Ephys is performed in WT and SLITRK3 KO mice.\n\n- \"The full-length cDNAs for mouse Slitrk1 (clone ID: mKIAA1910), Slitrk2 (40060548), Slitrk3 (6844461), Slitrk4 (40096585), Slitrk6 (4832410J21) and human PTPδ (40027582) were purchased from Kazusa DNA Research Institute, \"",
